                <h3>Barriers to treating childhood mental health disorders</h3>
                <br><br>
                <p>It can be difficult to understand mental health disorders in children because normal childhood development is a process that involves change.
                    <p> Additionally, the symptoms of a disorder may differ depending on a child's age, and children may not be able to explain how they feel or why they are behaving a certain way.</p>

                    <p>Concerns about the stigma associated with mental illness, the use of medications, and the cost or logistical challenges of treatment might also prevent parents from seeking care for a child who has a suspected mental illness.</p>

