                “The Basic Theory of the Mind” is a physical theory about the mind and its phenomena, such as consciousness and qualia. It also involves related matters including the hard problem of consciousness, the explanatory gap, variable qualia, p-zombies, and free will. This theory is a scientifically verifiable theory – it is based on physical evidence and provides experimentally testable predictions.
              </p>
